author: woolfel
msg: the access log sampler now only checks the classes when the
user first enters it. If a user simply loads a test plan and
runs, it is possible the sampler will fail silently.
should consider adding logging to the sampler.

author: woolfel
msg: changed the implementation so that the sampler does not
handle any gui stuff as suggested by Mike.
the downside of thing is if a person puts an invalid class
in either field, the sampler will fail silently.
